modules.description: Handles parsing and serialization of HTTP cookies according to RFC 6265, supporting domain, path, secure, and expiration attributes. Operates on structured cookie data including name-value pairs, flags, and metadata. Used to manage session state in web applications and ensure compliance when interacting with HTTP servers.

Represents HTTP cookie same-site policies with values that enforce restrictions on how cookies are sent with cross-site requests. Provides equality checks, comparisons, and serialization to cookie strings for policy enforcement. Supports specific policies like "none", "lax", and "strict" in web application security contexts.

Provides functions to construct, parse, and serialize HTTP cookies, including handling attributes like name, value, path, domain, expiration, and security flags. Works with strings, option types, and Ptime.t for date handling, and supports parsing from and generating values for HTTP headers. Enables accurate representation of cookies in both request and response contexts, ensuring compliance with RFC6265.
